         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶ 3/11/74 ¶  ¶ It affords me much pleasure, dear Sir Henry, to send you a few geographical notes on some less known parts of the Samoan Islands, written by the Rev G. Brown. ¶  ¶ The Rev. Ge...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">74.11.03a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Henry Rawlinson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Royal Geographical Society, London, Archives, JMS/18/67.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Addressee inferred: Sir Henry Rawlinson was President of the RGS in 1874-5.</p>
               </note>Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">3/11/74</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It affords me much pleasure, dear Sir Henry, to send you a few geographical notes on some less known parts of the Samoan Islands, written by the Rev G. Brown.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See George Brown to M, 2 November 1874 (in this edition as 74-11-02b).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Rev. Gentleman in his various journeys as a leading member of the Wesleyan Mission, has made many important scientific observations, particularly in zoology.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Many of George Brown's collections were described between 1877 and 1881 by specialists at the British Museum, for example a series of papers in the 1877 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London</seg>. He also presented live specimens to the Zoological Society of London (see, for example, the Blue-eyed Cockatoo from New Britain in the society's <seg style="font-style: italic; ">List of the vertebrated animals now or lately living in the gardens of the Zoological Society of London</seg>,<seg style="font-style: italic; "> </seg>8th edition, 1883, p. 308).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I would be glad, if the Royal Geographic Society elected him as an ordinary FRGS. You may rest assured, that this will much encourage this worthy divine to advance also geographic interests while in the performance of his ecclesiastic duties.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>George Brown was not elected FRGS until 1877; see Certificates of Candidates for Election, 22 January 1877 and 14 May 1877.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Let me remain your very regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg style="">Ferd von Mueller</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">Rev. Geo Brown. </seg>&amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Samoa.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Adr. Rev B. Chapman,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Secretary to the Wesleyan Mission Society,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Book Depot</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">King's Street</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sydney</p>
         </div>
